Governor David Umahi of Ebonyi State at the weekend inaugurated a 32-member steering committee of the open government partnership to actualise action plan for 2018-2020. Umahi, while inaugurating the committee, represented by his deputy, Dr. Eric Kelechi Igwe, restated his commitment towards maintaining transparency and accountability in governance.He said that government had always partnered with anti-corruption agencies and would always adopt programmes that will give value for money in terms of utilisation of scarce resources to develop the state. The governor, who described the programme as a unique, said the partnership would be sustained for the good of Ebonyi people. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .